about.summary: A MkDocs plugin that injects the mkdocs.yml extra variables into the markdown template

name: mkdocs-markdownextradata-plugin
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "mkdocs-markdownextradata-plugin" %}
{% set version = "0.0.6" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8a886706089bbfc022e3fd772a5d1edd399de4d587fc1521d7baa0519e85326b

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv "

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.5
    - setuptools
  run:
    - mkdocs >=0.17
    - python >=3.5
    - setuptools

test:
  imports:
    - markdownextradata

about:
  home: https://github.com/rosscdh/mkdocs-markdownextradata-plugin/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.md
  summary: A MkDocs plugin that injects the mkdocs.yml extra variables into the markdown template
  doc_url: http://www.mkdocs.org/user-guide/plugins/ 
  dev_url: https://github.com/rosscdh/mkdocs-markdownextradata-plugin/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - monaldoj
